intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to: 
Analyse critically computer vision algorithms and applications based on knowledge of image representation, image formation and basic processing techniques;
Implement feature extraction and object recognition algorithms;
Critically evaluate the basic geometric concepts in 3D computer vision and employed in recovery of 3D surfaces from stereo-pair images, or motion fields from image sequences;
Demonstrate the ability to apply the rudiments of information theory and basic image compression                                     techniques to the design of image coding/decoding algorithms;
Demonstrate competence in the use of the programming languages for vision-based applications prototyping.  Demonstrate competence in the application of the key current image analysis libraries.
